author: sussman
msg: Make 'svn lock nonexistentURL' work over ra_dav.
Even though we don't support locking nonexistent paths, it's still
possible for a lock to be orphaned -- left behind even after the file
is gone.  lock_tests.py #9 demonstrates this (simply commit the
deletion of a locked file, using the --no-unlock option), but also
shows that 'svn unlock URL' can remove the orphaned lock.
Anyway, this fixes lock_tests.py #9 over ra_dav.
* subversion/mod_dav_svn/repos.c
(dav_svn_prep_regular):   work around a shortcoming in mod_dav.
* subversion/mod_dav_svn/liveprops.c
(dav_svn_insert_prop):  return the VCC and baseline-relative-path
props even on nonexistent resources.
